The White House Press Secretary has released a statement expressing concern over the charging and continued detainment of Alan Gross. Gross has been held in Cuba for the past 14 months and has been denied his freedom. The statement criticizes the decision by Cuban authorities, stating that it further adds to the injustice experienced by Gross, who was working to increase the flow of information to and from the Cuban people. The Press Secretary calls for Gross' immediate release and expresses concern for his well-being and that of his family.